Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Conan Episode 991 "The \NAutomatic Tragedy (Part Two)"
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,[OP]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.64,0:00:02.98,Fusaya,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,1)}Oide Fusaya (22) \NOide Family Eldest Son
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.76,0:00:06.54,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Hired to find the culprit who \Nkilled Oide Fusaya-san's father,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.85,0:00:07.61,Raita,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,1)}Oide Raita (58) \NFusaya's Father
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.54,0:00:11.46,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}the old man and I tracked down the thief \Nwho burglarized the Oide family home
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.46,0:00:15.87,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}around the time of death of Fusaya-san's father Raita-san, Taira Yasushi.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.49,0:00:16.66,Yasushi,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,1)}Taira Yasushi (33) \NEngineering Firm Employee
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.10,0:00:22.37,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,However, Taira claimed he only burglarized the house while Raita-san was asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.25,0:00:26.92,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Was it Taira who murdered Raita-san
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.21,0:00:31.51,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,and set the gears of tragedy \Nin motion for the Oide family?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.35,0:00:33.53,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Or was it...?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.13,0:00:42.02,DCItalic,RAITA,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, Fusaya.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.76,0:00:51.78,DCItalic,RAITA,0000,0000,0000,,Fusaya, where have you been?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.04,0:00:57.03,DCItalic,RAITA,0000,0000,0000,,We're almost there, Fusaya.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.52,0:00:59.53,DCItalic,RAITA,0000,0000,0000,,Where do you think you're going, Fusaya?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.74,0:01:09.63,DCItalic,RAITA,0000,0000,0000,,Fusaya, come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.05,0:01:16.51,DCMain,FUSAYA,0000,0000,0000,,Don't laugh at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.05,0:01:19.02,DCMain,FUSAYA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm pretty serious about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.77,0:01:24.62,DCMain,FUSAYA,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be back, Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.91,0:01:30.68,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Find the question that solves the mystery!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.68,0:01:32.83,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Apply miraculous detective skills \Nto the secrets of the heart!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.83,0:01:34.69,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A series of tragedies befall a family!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.94,0:01:37.26,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Identify the culprit and \Nstop the gears from turning!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.26,0:01:38.90,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Always determining the one truth
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.90,0:01:40.87,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,with the body of a child \Nand the mind of an adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.87,0:01:43.16,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,his name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.97,0:03:28.97,DCEpTitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(399,1)}The Automatic Tragedy \N(Part Two)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.63,0:03:26.64,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,"The Automatic Tragedy, Part Two!"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.25,0:03:36.86,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,If this case was the premeditated \Nmurder of Oide Raita,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.35,0:03:40.20,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,that would make what Taira \Nsaid rather curious.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.97,0:03:43.17,DCItalic,TAIRA,0000,0000,0000,,He was snoring in his sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.17,0:03:44.66,DCItalic,TAIRA,0000,0000,0000,,Right on the floor here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.66,0:03:46.12,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That testimony.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.82,0:03:49.62,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.62,0:03:50.48,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.48,0:03:52.12,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Did you figure something out?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.12,0:03:55.35,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't figured anything out, so I'm \Ngoing back to the Oide family home.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.35,0:03:56.38,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.03,0:04:00.13,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Inspiration will surely strike \Nif we go to the crime scene,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.13,0:04:04.13,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,the same way we figured out \NTaira Yasushi was the burglar.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.40,0:04:10.05,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,So, why are we taking the train \Ninstead of a rental car today?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.05,0:04:14.65,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Because today, taking public \Ntransportation is good luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.64,0:04:14.65,Transportation,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,This week for you! \NTaking public \Ntransportation is good luck!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.97,0:04:16.66,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,We're relying on fortune telling now?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.66,0:04:19.65,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, is this what he was \Nreading so intently earlier?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.22,0:04:24.66,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,If we'd taken the train yesterday, \Nwe might've solved the case already.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.91,0:04:28.10,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Now then.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.58,0:04:30.64,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Fusaya-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.64,0:04:32.94,DCMain,FUSAYA,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-san, what are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.94,0:04:36.17,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I'd examine your place again today.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.40,0:04:40.35,DCMain,FUSAYA,0000,0000,0000,,I see. In that case, my \Nsister went to the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.35,0:04:40.96,DCMain,FUSAYA,0000,0000,0000,,I'll give you the key.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.96,0:04:42.49,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.49,0:04:45.99,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Fusaya-san, you're dressed rather formally.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.99,0:04:47.74,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have a date or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.74,0:04:50.69,DCMain,FUSAYA,0000,0000,0000,,No. I've got an interview.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.69,0:04:52.40,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Your necktie is crooked.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.72,0:04:59.63,DCMain,FUSAYA,0000,0000,0000,,My father was worried that I couldn't \Nfind a job until the very end.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.20,0:05:03.19,DCMain,FUSAYA,0000,0000,0000,,I thought doing whatever it takes to get one \Nwould be a good way to honor his memory.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.46,0:05:07.49,DCMain,FUSAYA,0000,0000,0000,,They're closed today, but I asked \Nthem to make some time for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.00,0:05:11.68,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure they'll understand if you \Nexplain your feelings to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.68,0:05:12.86,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,They surely will.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.86,0:05:14.33,DCMain,FUSAYA,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.71,0:05:18.33,DCMain,FUSAYA,0000,0000,0000,,All that's left is to \Nfind my father's killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.69,0:05:23.29,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Leave it all to me, the great detective Mori \NKogoro, to handle the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.29,0:05:25.72,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You should focus on your interview.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.25,0:05:27.34,DCMain,FUSAYA,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.40,0:05:30.97,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,So, we came all the way here...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.15,0:05:37.69,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm still not getting any ideas.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.69,0:05:39.48,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's strange, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.93,0:05:41.08,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What is?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.08,0:05:44.99,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,When Taira snuck into the \Nhouse to steal the money,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.40,0:05:48.97,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Oide Raita-san was sleeping on \Nthe floor around here, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.97,0:05:49.64,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.64,0:05:52.99,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,They have a sofa, so why was \Nhe sleeping on the hard floor?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.34,0:05:56.13,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,He was probably overcome \Nby extreme sleepiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.13,0:06:00.25,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,When I've had a lot to drink, I end \Nup sleeping wherever when I come home.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.69,0:06:05.83,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But Raita-san was looking for Fusaya-san \Nthat day, so that couldn't have been it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.83,0:06:07.41,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe he drank his cares away.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.41,0:06:09.26,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He's not you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.48,0:06:13.59,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, he must've \Nbeen really tired or...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.35,0:06:15.64,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Sleeping pills.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.24,0:06:18.98,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, the culprit
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.98,0:06:22.15,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,secretly drugged Raita with sleeping \Npills before Taira snuck into the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.90,0:06:28.55,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,After confirming they'd taken \Neffect, they tried to kill him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.55,0:06:30.02,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,But then...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.53,0:06:32.16,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Taira snuck into the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.91,0:06:36.76,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The culprit hid somewhere and \Nwatched to see what he'd do.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.76,0:06:40.21,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,After watching Taira burglarize \Nand flee the house,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.55,0:06:45.34,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,they killed Raita as planned.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.24,0:06:52.57,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, why did the culprit \Nbother putting him to sleep?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.57,0:06:55.22,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Because he would've resisted otherwise.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.22,0:06:57.68,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, the culprit is a weak person.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.26,0:06:59.56,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Like a woman?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.56,0:07:04.69,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I hate to imagine it,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.34,0:07:07.18,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,but is that a possibility?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.84,0:07:10.38,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,A woman? Could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.38,0:07:12.39,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,All right. In that case...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.82,0:07:13.53,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Mister?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.53,0:07:15.37,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,We'll have to go to the hospital to check.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.80,0:07:18.45,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds like he's zeroed \Nin on the culprit again.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.56,0:07:21.79,DCMain,AN,0000,0000,0000,,What? A woman?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.79,0:07:22.64,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.64,0:07:26.54,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Did Raita mention having \Nproblems with anyone?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.21,0:07:26.67,An,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,460)}Oide An (24) \NFusaya's Older Sister
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.21,0:07:26.67,Io,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,460)}Oide Io (56) \NFusaya's Mother
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.93,0:07:28.88,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,She's a young woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.88,0:07:30.52,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.52,0:07:32.40,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,She was there yesterday by the station.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.40,0:07:34.50,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,A very suspicious-looking woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.50,0:07:35.05,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.49,0:07:41.02,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's who you meant.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.02,0:07:43.29,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Who did you think I was talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.76,0:07:44.31,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.73,0:07:49.66,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,She's around your age, wears sunglasses, \Nand has a mole right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.66,0:07:50.07,DCMain,AN,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.32,0:07:53.18,DCMain,AN,0000,0000,0000,,Do you mean Kuremi?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.18,0:07:54.54,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,So you know who she is?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.54,0:07:55.57,DCMain,AN,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.77,0:07:57.32,DCMain,AN,0000,0000,0000,,Soho Kuremi-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.32,0:07:58.72,DCMain,AN,0000,0000,0000,,She was my classmate in middle school.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.72,0:08:01.65,DCMain,AN,0000,0000,0000,,Last night she came here to visit us.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.65,0:08:03.27,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,She's your friend?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.27,0:08:05.08,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,She was here last night?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.30,0:08:06.03,DCMain,AN,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.03,0:08:09.06,DCMain,AN,0000,0000,0000,,When I ran into her the other day, \NI told her I'd gotten engaged.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.06,0:08:10.84,DCMain,AN,0000,0000,0000,,She seemed very happy for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.09,0:08:14.51,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Where can I find this Soho Kuremi-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.65,0:08:16.63,DCMain,AN,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hold on.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.63,0:08:18.41,DCMain,AN,0000,0000,0000,,She gave me her business card the other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.41,0:08:19.26,DCMain,AN,0000,0000,0000,,This is it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.26,0:08:19.93,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.93,0:08:23.44,Pharmacist,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Tebai West Pharmacy \NPharmacist \NSoho Kuremi
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.36,0:08:23.44,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,She's a pharmacist?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.77,0:08:26.79,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, she could've \Nacquired some sleeping pills.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.79,0:08:28.59,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for your help.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.59,0:08:29.44,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Now then.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.71,0:08:31.00,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.45,0:08:33.07,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, Mister.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.07,0:08:34.53,DCMain,AN,0000,0000,0000,,Does Kuremi know something?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.53,0:08:37.37,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe there's something \Nhe wants her help with.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.89,0:08:41.45,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,On the day of the incident, when \Nthe two of you returned home,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.45,0:08:45.87,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Raita-san was in the living room angry about \NFusaya-san running away from home, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.06,0:08:47.52,DCMain,IO,0000,0000,0000,,Not in the living room.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.52,0:08:50.41,DCMain,IO,0000,0000,0000,,He was at the bottom of the \Nstairs just inside the entrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.41,0:08:51.32,DCMain,AN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.32,0:08:54.88,DCMain,AN,0000,0000,0000,,Dad was really angry while \Nhe was fixing the shelf.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.88,0:08:59.30,DCMain,IO,0000,0000,0000,,Fusaya leaving home must \Nhave really come as a shock.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.30,0:09:03.34,DCMain,IO,0000,0000,0000,,Remember that last phone call he made to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.34,0:09:04.77,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Did something happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.77,0:09:05.72,DCMain,AN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.72,0:09:08.94,DCMain,AN,0000,0000,0000,,He called to ask if we'd found Fusaya.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.12,0:09:11.56,DCItalic,RAITA,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.56,0:09:14.22,DCItalic,RAITA,0000,0000,0000,,You haven't even found anyone who's seen him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.94,0:09:18.95,DCItalic,RAITA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry. I suddenly feel sleepy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.95,0:09:20.62,DCItalic,RAITA,0000,0000,0000,,The rest is up to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.62,0:09:22.95,DCItalic,AN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.29,0:09:28.45,DCMain,AN,0000,0000,0000,,Since his voice was so indistinct, I \Nthought it must have really gotten to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.45,0:09:31.96,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What time did you receive \Nthat final phone call?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.20,0:09:33.87,DCMain,AN,0000,0000,0000,,Around 3:30.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.81,0:09:35.78,DCMain,AN,0000,0000,0000,,Is something the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.78,0:09:37.22,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.37,0:09:40.10,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I'll pass on your story.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.10,0:09:41.08,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.22,0:09:43.22,DCNote,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Tebai West Pharmacy
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.82,0:09:45.84,DCMain,KUREMI,0000,0000,0000,,Take care.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.84,0:09:46.80,DCMain,CUSTEROM,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.36,0:09:48.48,DCMain,KUREMI,0000,0000,0000,,Next customer, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.65,0:09:52.07,Kuremi,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,460)}Soho Kuremi (24) \NPharmacist
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.71,0:09:51.14,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}You're Soho Kuremi-san, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.78,0:09:56.22,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You seem to recognize me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.22,0:10:00.60,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You know who I am, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.67,0:10:08.36,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Soho Kuremi-san, after running \Ninto your former classmate,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.36,0:10:10.88,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,you heard about her engagement.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.40,0:10:14.33,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,She was engaged to the \Nson of a wealthy family.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.33,0:10:16.88,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Jealous that she was marrying into money,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.12,0:10:19.89,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,you plotted to inflict misfortune upon her.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.51,0:10:21.21,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.64,0:10:23.28,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There's something odd about this culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.70,0:10:27.80,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,By making her father Raita a murder victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.59,0:10:33.65,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,That day, you visited the Oide family home
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.83,0:10:38.90,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,and secretly drugged Raita using sleeping \Npills you procured from your workplace.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.48,0:10:42.51,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The sudden sleepiness Raita mentioned
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.51,0:10:44.66,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,was due to the sleeping pills \Nhe was given taking effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.25,0:10:49.16,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, Raita must've fallen asleep \Nimmediately afterwards just past 4 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.35,0:10:54.52,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But he was killed 30 minutes later at 4:30.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.23,0:10:57.83,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,They successfully put \Nhim to sleep as planned,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.83,0:11:00.43,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,so why didn't the culprit act right away?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.44,0:11:03.29,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That 30 minute delay.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.29,0:11:04.66,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What does it mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.66,0:11:06.55,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm beat.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.55,0:11:09.56,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe I got injured after \Ngetting caught up in that accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.79,0:11:14.36,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,Although I did receive a bunch \Nof money in compensation.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.89,0:11:17.94,DCMain,WOMAN,0000,0000,0000,,That kind of thinking will get you killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.17,0:11:21.39,DCMain,WOMAN,0000,0000,0000,,Your injuries may not have been \Nserious, but it's still a concussion.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.23,0:11:29.29,DCMain,KUREMI,0000,0000,0000,,That's what you thought of me?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.29,0:11:29.71,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.93,0:11:32.02,DCMain,KUREMI,0000,0000,0000,,It's true that I was jealous.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.02,0:11:35.21,DCMain,KUREMI,0000,0000,0000,,I think she got what she \Ndeserved with this case.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.43,0:11:38.78,DCMain,KUREMI,0000,0000,0000,,When you started showing up \Neverywhere I went, I laughed.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.78,0:11:42.01,DCMain,KUREMI,0000,0000,0000,,I thought they must really be struggling \Nif they hired a famous detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.01,0:11:45.72,DCMain,KUREMI,0000,0000,0000,,But it sounds like you're actually a hack.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.72,0:11:47.14,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.31,0:11:51.56,DCMain,KUREMI,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't fallen so low that I'd commit \Nmurder over something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.92,0:11:53.94,DCMain,KUREMI,0000,0000,0000,,Could you not make a fool of me?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.94,0:11:58.70,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Then why did you keep showing up \Nwherever that family went yesterday?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.70,0:12:01.84,DCMain,KUREMI,0000,0000,0000,,Is watching them from a distance \Nand pretending to visit them
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.84,0:12:03.62,DCMain,KUREMI,0000,0000,0000,,so I could laugh at them a crime?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.13,0:12:06.87,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It's certainly true that \Nyou're behaving suspiciously.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.08,0:12:10.06,DCMain,KUREMI,0000,0000,0000,,Don't treat me like a criminal when \Nyou don't even have any evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.06,0:12:12.61,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Then at least help me with my investigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.61,0:12:14.04,DCMain,KUREMI,0000,0000,0000,,You're so persistent.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.55,0:12:17.85,DCMain,KUREMI,0000,0000,0000,,I'll give you some special information \Nif you'll leave me alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.85,0:12:19.46,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.68,0:12:21.58,DCMain,KUREMI,0000,0000,0000,,I saw a suspicious person exit that house
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.58,0:12:26.08,DCMain,KUREMI,0000,0000,0000,,on the day of the incident \Nwhen the 4:30 PM notice played.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.08,0:12:28.08,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What? What kind of person?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.08,0:12:32.48,DCMain,KUREMI,0000,0000,0000,,A short man wearing a hat with \Nshaggy hair and a prominent nose.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.10,0:12:38.34,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Shaggy hair, prominent nose, wearing a hat,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.34,0:12:40.01,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,and short.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.74,0:12:43.40,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,That's Taira.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.58,0:12:46.02,DCMain,KUREMI,0000,0000,0000,,What? He's not the culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.02,0:12:49.93,DCMain,KUREMI,0000,0000,0000,,I held onto that information so \Nthe family would owe me a favor.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.93,0:12:50.78,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.78,0:12:54.51,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Was he carrying a large bag of some kind?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.51,0:12:55.92,DCMain,KUREMI,0000,0000,0000,,A bag, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.62,0:13:01.33,DCMain,KUREMI,0000,0000,0000,,I think all he had with him \Nwas a small shoulder bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.40,0:13:06.29,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Which means Taira didn't \Ntake the weapon with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.29,0:13:08.43,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,He's starting to sound innocent.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.43,0:13:10.31,DCMain,KUREMI,0000,0000,0000,,Satisfied?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.62,0:13:15.86,DCMain,KUREMI,0000,0000,0000,,Good luck finding the real \Nculprit, Mr. Great Detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.52,0:13:17.81,DCMain,KUREMI,0000,0000,0000,,Later.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.13,0:13:20.11,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.19,0:13:23.57,PoliceStation,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Tebai Police Station
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.01,0:13:23.57,DCMain,TAGIRI,0000,0000,0000,,What? From the autopsy?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.79,0:13:26.95,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. He asked me to check in a hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.11,0:13:30.53,Yoshia,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,460)}Lieutenant Tagiri Yoshia (45) \NTebai Station Officer
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.22,0:13:30.52,DCMain,TAGIRI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}If it was Mori-san's request, \Nthen I suppose I can show you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.52,0:13:33.86,DCMain,TAGIRI,0000,0000,0000,,But will you understand \Nwhat you're looking at?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.86,0:13:36.96,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I'll tell him exactly \Nwhat I saw. Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.96,0:13:37.96,DCMain,TAGIRI,0000,0000,0000,,Will you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.97,0:13:46.76,Autopsy,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Single blow only
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.76,0:13:48.51,Autopsy,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Caused by acute epidural hematoma
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.31,0:13:48.51,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I knew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.75,0:13:52.62,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The person who set the gears of tragedy \Nin motion for the Oide family was...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.24,0:14:02.45,DCMain,AN,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.45,0:14:04.73,DCMain,FUSUYA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I really got the job.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.73,0:14:06.27,DCMain,AN,0000,0000,0000,,That's great.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.86,0:14:08.50,DCMain,AN,0000,0000,0000,,Now Dad can rest in peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.74,0:14:12.03,DCMain,IO,0000,0000,0000,,You came, Fusaya.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.03,0:14:14.76,DCMain,FUSAYA,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, Mom. Did I wake you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.76,0:14:15.75,DCMain,IO,0000,0000,0000,,It's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.24,0:14:19.10,DCMain,IO,0000,0000,0000,,I was just dreaming about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.10,0:14:21.88,DCMain,IO,0000,0000,0000,,We were all celebrating you landing a job.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.88,0:14:24.30,DCMain,AN,0000,0000,0000,,Mom, your dream came true.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.30,0:14:25.76,DCMain,IO,0000,0000,0000,,What? You mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.60,0:14:29.51,DCMain,FUSAYA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. They're going to hire me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.68,0:14:34.18,DCMain,IO,0000,0000,0000,,That's great. That's so great.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.30,0:14:39.03,DCMain,FUSAYA,0000,0000,0000,,Hello? Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.49,0:14:41.40,DCMain,FUSAYA,0000,0000,0000,,Really? Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.09,0:14:44.05,DCMain,FUSAYA,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I'll head back immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.51,0:14:45.40,DCMain,AN,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.68,0:14:46.95,DCMain,FUSAYA,0000,0000,0000,,That was Mori-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.95,0:14:48.53,DCMain,FUSAYA,0000,0000,0000,,He figured out who the culprit is.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.51,0:14:52.03,DCMain,FUSAYA,0000,0000,0000,,Hiring him was the right choice after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.32,0:14:55.73,DCMain,FUSAYA,0000,0000,0000,,You're getting married, and I got a job.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.73,0:14:59.04,DCMain,FUSAYA,0000,0000,0000,,The gears of tragedy will \Nfinally stop turning now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.52,0:15:02.18,DCMain,FUSAYA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to go hear what he has to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.04,0:15:08.17,DCMain,IO,0000,0000,0000,,Is it true?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.40,0:15:11.51,DCMain,IO,0000,0000,0000,,After all, it's only been a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.32,0:15:14.55,DCMain,AN,0000,0000,0000,,Well, he is a great detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.70,0:15:17.18,DCMain,IO,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.34,0:15:22.48,DCMain,IO,0000,0000,0000,,There's no harm in praying to god \Nor asking great detectives for help.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.48,0:15:24.69,DCMain,AN,0000,0000,0000,,What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.02,0:15:27.16,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I'll meet you at your home.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.69,0:15:33.07,Oide,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Oide
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.50,0:15:38.37,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Where have you been?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.37,0:15:39.61,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.61,0:15:42.33,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,How did things go with the suspicious woman?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.54,0:15:44.29,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,She was just suspicious, nothing more.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.29,0:15:46.38,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't find a single piece of evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.38,0:15:53.59,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Speaking of evidence, they didn't \Nfind any sleeping pills in Raita-san's body.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.59,0:15:55.19,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,No alcohol either.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.19,0:15:56.47,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.76,0:16:00.51,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,That means my deduction \Nis fundamentally wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.91,0:16:04.52,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, how do you even know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.56,0:16:09.28,DCMain,COANN,0000,0000,0000,,Lieutenant Tagiri asked me to tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.12,0:16:13.35,DCMain,FUSAYA,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.93,0:16:16.15,DCMain,FUSAYA,0000,0000,0000,,You truly are the country's \Ngreatest detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.58,0:16:20.14,DCMain,FUSAYA,0000,0000,0000,,Who is it? Who's the true culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.14,0:16:20.58,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.77,0:16:22.96,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, I, uh—
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.14,0:16:25.03,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm still working on that...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.09,0:16:28.71,DCMain,FUSAYA,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.71,0:16:30.58,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Let's figure that out together.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.99,0:16:34.22,DCMain,FUSAYA,0000,0000,0000,,Is this the rumored Sleeping Kogoro?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.81,0:16:37.72,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Allow me to describe my reasoning.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.66,0:16:44.95,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The culprit thought to have snuck into \Nthis house and killed your father
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.44,0:16:49.23,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,never existed in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.46,0:16:52.93,DCMain,FUSAYA,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean, Mori-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.34,0:16:57.74,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Before I explain the truth, I'd like \Nto confirm something with you first.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.06,0:17:04.25,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The morning of the incident, Raita returned \Njust as you were leaving the house
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.25,0:17:09.25,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,in order to avoid troubling \Nyour sister and her fiancee.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.61,0:17:15.64,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,He returned to speak with you about your \Nfuture, but the two of you got into a fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.21,0:17:19.51,DCMain,FUSAYA,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. Why are you \Nbringing that up now?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.74,0:17:23.65,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Was your fight with your \Nfather rather intense?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.65,0:17:24.52,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,For example...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.86,0:17:29.27,DCItalic,AN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Dad was really angry \Nwhile he was fixing the shelf.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.61,0:17:33.80,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Your sister was referring to \Nthe hanging shelf up there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.80,0:17:35.78,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,And your fight was violent \Nenough that it broke.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.28,0:17:39.88,DCMain,FUSAYA,0000,0000,0000,,We got into a scuffle, and \NI threw my father off of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.88,0:17:44.79,DCMain,FUSAYA,0000,0000,0000,,His back struck the wall, \Ncausing the shelf to fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.33,0:17:48.71,DCMain,FUSAYA,0000,0000,0000,,I left while that was happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.28,0:17:51.04,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,And that was around 10 AM.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.04,0:17:56.04,DCMain,FUSAYA,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. More importantly, what do \Nyou mean, there's no culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.04,0:17:56.80,DCMain,FUSAYA,0000,0000,0000,,My father is—
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.80,0:17:59.68,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Dead. You've heard the cause \Nof death, haven't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.85,0:18:02.68,DCMain,FUSAYA,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, but I'd never heard the term before.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.68,0:18:05.56,Autopsy,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Caused by acute epidural hematoma
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.08,0:18:05.56,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Acute epidural hematoma.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.74,0:18:09.10,DCMain,FUSAYA,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I believe that's what it's called.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.10,0:18:11.44,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,They're quite tricky.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.44,0:18:16.24,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Often the moment a person strikes their \Nhead and their time of death don't match.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.24,0:18:16.69,DCMain,FUSAYA,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.04,0:18:22.00,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,People who strike their head and \Nfall unconscious due to a concussion
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.00,0:18:25.96,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,often recover quickly and appear totally \Nlucid as though nothing happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.96,0:18:29.71,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,This is known as a lucid interval.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.79,0:18:29.71,DCNote,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Lucid Interval
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.96,0:18:33.62,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The state can persist for three to six hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.11,0:18:38.63,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,However, they then rapidly lose \Nconsciousness and die shortly later.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.00,0:18:41.13,DCMain,FUSAYA,0000,0000,0000,,You're saying that's what \Nhappened to my father?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.13,0:18:42.85,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Most likely.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.49,0:18:45.72,DCMain,FUSAYA,0000,0000,0000,,You mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.93,0:18:49.28,DCItalic,RAITA,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you show a little more \Nconsideration for your family?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.11,0:18:53.06,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You and Raita got into a scuffle here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.70,0:19:05.55,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The hanging shelf fell, and its \Ncorner struck Raita on the head.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.26,0:19:09.50,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,That's when the acute \Nepidural hematoma developed.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.40,0:19:13.36,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Raita probably lost \Nconsciousness for a moment,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.85,0:19:15.88,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,but once the lucid interval began,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.28,0:19:19.02,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,he got up as though nothing had happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.02,0:19:20.01,DCItalic,RAITA,0000,0000,0000,,Fusaya!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.01,0:19:21.89,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,After that, he fixed the shelf,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.66,0:19:25.51,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,and helped your other family \Nmembers look for you,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.78,0:19:31.64,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,but eventually he was overcome by \Nfatigue as he lost consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.30,0:19:35.71,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Unaware that a burglar \Nhad entered his home...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.94,0:19:40.65,DCItalic,ANNOUNCE,0000,0000,0000,,The time is 4:30.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.65,0:19:43.79,DCItalic,ANNOUNCE,0000,0000,0000,,Please be careful as you \Nreturn to your homes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.79,0:19:45.35,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,...he died.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.93,0:19:50.27,DCMain,FUSAYA,0000,0000,0000,,But that's just one theory, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.86,0:19:55.59,DCMain,FUSAYA,0000,0000,0000,,There could be a true culprit who \Nsnuck in after that burglar fled
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.29,0:19:59.09,DCMain,FUSAYA,0000,0000,0000,,and bludgeoned my father to death!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.52,0:20:00.84,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,That's not possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.36,0:20:07.60,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,There were no wounds on Raita's head aside \Nfrom the one caused by the fatal blow.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.59,0:20:07.60,Autopsy,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Single blow only
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.25,0:20:11.51,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,And when the shelf was examined earlier,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.99,0:20:14.60,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,it matched Raita's injury.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.25,0:20:17.97,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,That's the truth, Fusaya-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.93,0:20:22.81,DCMain,FUSAYA,0000,0000,0000,,Which means my father died
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.34,0:20:26.52,DCMain,FUSAYA,0000,0000,0000,,because of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.62,0:20:34.25,DCMain,IO,0000,0000,0000,,I prayed at this shrine yesterday \Nevening and this morning, too,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.91,0:20:40.38,DCMain,IO,0000,0000,0000,,for Mori-san to find the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.38,0:20:42.13,DCMain,AN,0000,0000,0000,,Your prayers were answered.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.64,0:20:47.14,DCMain,IO,0000,0000,0000,,Now we can finally begin \Npreparing for your wedding.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.14,0:20:52.89,DCMain,AN,0000,0000,0000,,Fusaya has found his way, and you'll \Nbe able to leave the hospital tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.63,0:20:58.04,DCMain,IO,0000,0000,0000,,The light has finally fallen on our family.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.04,0:20:58.89,DCMain,AN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.82,0:22:43.94,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You can count on me, Fusaya-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.38,0:22:49.98,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I promise I'll save the entire Oide family.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.48,0:22:57.25,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I, the great detective Mori Kogoro, so swear.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.43,0:23:04.40,DCItalic,FUSAYA,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-san, it's my job to stop the \Ngears of tragedy from turning.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.74,0:23:08.90,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Fusaya-kun, you should decide \Nhow you'll live for yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.20,0:23:10.64,DCItalic,FUSAYA,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.64,0:23:12.66,DCItalic,FUSAYA,0000,0000,0000,,For my dad, my sister, my mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.84,0:23:14.66,DCItalic,FUSAYA,0000,0000,0000,,For my entire family.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.36,0:23:17.27,DCItalic,FUSAYA,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.04,0:23:22.29,PoliceStation2,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Tebai Police Station
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.19,0:23:28.24,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,After all, I'm the country's \Ngreatest detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.24,0:23:29.97,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Mister.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.20,0:23:32.88,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's time for the last train.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.38,0:23:38.03,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, old man. Wake up already.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.86,0:23:44.98,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Taking public transportation \Nis good luck? Yeah, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.98,0:24:09.01,DCEpPreview,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Episode Preview
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.62,0:23:47.86,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,We've arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.49,0:23:51.36,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Well? Pretty tasteful, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.30,0:23:56.37,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,I had a bite, but it's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.77,0:23:58.07,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Say, "Ah."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.09,0:24:00.87,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.00,0:24:04.07,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.07,0:24:06.13,DCMain,NONAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I-It's an emergency.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.87,0:24:08.10,DCMain,NONAKA,0000,0000,0000,,The manager...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.01,0:24:15.01,DCNextEp,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Murder at the Townhouse Café
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.43,0:24:13.13,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The next episode of Conan is \N"Murder at the Townhouse Café!"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.03,0:24:34.95,Hint,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Donuts
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.44,0:24:33.14,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Edogawa-kun, it's time for Conan's next hint.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.14,0:24:34.51,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Donuts!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.95,0:24:36.04,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Speaking of donuts...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.95,0:24:39.95,Don'tMiss,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Don't miss the next episode.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.04,0:24:37.53,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Deutsche beer plus peanuts?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.53,0:24:39.03,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Seriously? Who said that?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.03,0:24:39.80,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Huh?
